CARNATIC MUSIC, known as Karnāṭaka saṃgīta or Karnāṭaka saṅgītam in the South Indian languages,is a system of music commonly associated with south India,including the modern Indian states of Karnataka,Andhra Pradesh,Telangana,Kerela and Tamil Nadu.
